[b]Regime Transition Engine[/b] classifies the current market into one of seven regime states and reads how close it is to flipping into the next one — a single, stable read on "what kind of market is this right now" instead of another price-based oscillator.

[b]What it does[/b]

Every bar is scored across seven candidate regimes: Noise, Compression, Expansion, Trend Up, Trend Down, Exhaustion, and Reversion. The state only switches once a minimum dwell period has passed and the new candidate clearly outscores the active one — this keeps the read stable instead of flickering between states. A Transition Pressure oscillator then estimates how close the active state is to moving into its natural successor (Compression → Expansion, Expansion → Trend, Trend → Exhaustion, Exhaustion → Reversion).

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Seven-state regime classifier[/b] — Noise / Compression / Expansion / Trend Up / Trend Down / Exhaustion / Reversion
[*][b]Dwell + hysteresis debouncing[/b] — the active state only changes on a clear, sustained score edge
[*][b]Directional Transition Pressure oscillator[/b] — reads how close the market is to flipping regime
[*][b]State-change markers[/b] — Compression→Expansion, Expansion→Trend, Trend→Exhaustion, Exhaustion→Reversion
[*][b]Dashboard[/b] — active state, next-bias label, transition %, state age, and core diagnostic readouts
[/list]

[b]How to read it[/b]

The colored State Track and background shading show the currently active regime. The Directional Transition Pressure line rising toward its extremes signals the active regime is maturing toward its next stage; the dashboard's "Next Bias" field spells out what that stage is in plain language.

